<TITLE> Champions, runners-up in Friendship Cup Football to get Tk 3 lakh, 2 lakh </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 6 (bdnews24.com)  The champions and runners-up in the five-team Friendship Cup Football will be awarded Tk 3 lakh and Tk 2 lakh respectively. The decision was taken at the first meeting of the organising committee of the tournament held at National Sports Council (NSC) conference room Tuesday. The Friendship Cup Football, involving Mohammedan Sporting Club, Abahani Limited, Kolkata Mohammedan, NRT from Nepal and Muktijoddha Sangsad or a team from Malaysia, is scheduled for November 28 to December 10 at Bangabandhu National Stadium. The committee, however, will take the final decision on the fifth team of the tournament Wednesday. "We hope the tournament will be completed successfully as everyone is behind us," said organising committee chairman and Abahani director- in -charge Lt Colonel (retd) Kazi Shaheed Ahmed. "Such initiative will benefit country's football as everyone has extended his hand," said Bangladesh Football Federation (BFF) president and adviser of the tournament SA Sultan. "Our aim is to resurrect country's football along with building a bridge among players, organisers, patrons and sports administrators," said organising committee secretary Badal Roy. Roy said they have estimated Tk 60-65 lakh for the tournament as they plan to hand over participation money to the teams. The meeting also formed a financial committee with Anjan Kumar Chowdhury Pintu as its head. Former BFF general secretary Harunor Rashid, BFF vice presidents Sirajul Islam Bacchu, Abdur Rahim, Mohammedan general secretary Lokhman Hossain Bhuiyan, Abahani director Kazi Nabil Ahmed, Brothers general secretary Mizanuddin Ahmed, Shekh Russel KC president Nurul Alam Chowdhury, NSC secretary Aminul Islam, former footballers Jakaria Pintu, Golam Sarwar Tiup, Abdul Salam Murshedi, Sheikh Mohammad Aslam, Kaiser Hamid, Rummon Bin Wali Sabbir, Khurshid Alam Babul, Imtiaz Sultan Jony were, among others, present. 
